				<!-- start pageDataHeading -->
				<h1>Opting in to the post 1 July 2014 aged care means assessment arrangements 065-21050552</h1>
<ul id="tabs-primary"><li><a class="active students" href="../older-australians/065-21050552-01.html">Background</a></li><li><a href="../older-australians/065-21050552-03.html">Process</a></li><li><a href="../older-australians/065-21050552-05.html">Resources</a></li></ul>
				<!-- end pageDataHeading -->
				
				<!-- start pageDataContent -->
				<div id="bgtab" class="">
					
<div id="relatedMessagesDiv"></div>


					<div class="unitRight"><a href="javascript:expandCollapseSections()" id="toggleText" alt="Expand/Collapse all sections" title="Expand/Collapse all sections"><img src="../../supportingContent/images/icons/toggle_plus.gif"align="top" id="toggleImage"border="0" alt="Expand/Collapse all sections"width="16" height="16">Expand all</a></div><br><br>

					<body>
<a name="top" class="anchor"></a><div id="contentObp" class="main"><div id="topnav"></div>


<p>This document outlines how care recipients can choose to opt in to the post 1 July 2014 aged care means assessment arrangements. This process only applies to the Aged Care Payments Team (Aged Care and Allied Health Branch).</p>

<p></p>
<div class="twisty">
	
<a class="anchor" name="bp01_L2GT_Historical_SPAR"></a>
<h2 id="_Toc344898764">Historical SPARC process</h2>

	<div class="collapsible_container">
		<div class="block">

<p>The System for the Payment of Aged Residential Care (SPARC) is the legacy aged care payment system for residential care. SPARC is a view only system from 20 August 2022.</p>

<p>To view the legacy SPARC process, see the <a target="_blank" href="../older-australians/065-21050552-01.html?PageVersion=3072">historical version</a>.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>


<p></p>
<div class="twisty">
	
<a class="anchor" name="bp01_L2GT_Background"></a>
<h2 id="_Toc344898764">Background</h2>

	<div class="collapsible_container">
		<div class="block">

<p>Aged care means assessments determine the care recipient’s ability to contribute towards government-funded aged care services. There are different schemes in place depending on the date of entry into care. See <a href="../older-australians/065-09000000-01.html">Aged Care means assessment</a> for more details.</p>

<p></p>

<p>Care recipients (or their nominees) can opt in to the post 1 July 2014 means assessment scheme if they&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
were in a residential care service or receiving a home care package on 30 June 2014, and</li>
		<li>
have moved to a new service on or after 1 July 2014, and </li>
		<li>
have not spent more than 28 days outside of care (other than on approved leave)</li>
		</ul>
<p></p>

<p>Written details about the 1 July 2014 means assessment arrangement must be given to care recipients (or their nominees) who&#58;</p>
		<ul>		<li>
were in care on 30 June 2014, and </li>
		<li>
choose to opt in to the post 1 July 2014 means assessment scheme</li>
		</ul>
<p>This includes care recipients who are intending to move to a new service.</p>

<p></p>

<p>All care recipients who choose to opt in to the post 1 July 2014 means assessment scheme must give the new service a completed Continuing Care Recipient opting into the New Aged Care Arrangements from 1 July 2014 form (AC022) <strong>before</strong> they transfer into the new service.</p>

<p>See <a href="../older-australians/065-21050552-05.html">Resources</a> for links to&#58; </p>
		<ul>		<li>
the written details (New Arrangements for Aged Care from 1 July 2014 – Home Care and New Arrangements for Aged Care from 1 July 2014 – Residential Care), and</li>
		<li>
the AC022 form</li>
		</ul>
<p></p>

<p>The AC022 form must be submitted with the care recipient’s entry event via&#58; </p>
		<ul>		<li>
online (the Aged Care Provider Portal), or </li>
		<li>
manually (the Aged Care Entry Record form (AC021))</li>
		</ul>
<p></p>

<p>Online entry events that contain the care recipient’s decision to opt into the post 1 July 2014 means assessment scheme will be Held. Subject Matter Experts (SME) assess and process held entry events to determine if a valid AC022 form has been received by Services Australia. See <a href="../older-australians/065-13090040-01.html">Process residential care held event management in the Aged Care Staff Portal (ACSP)</a>.</p>

<p></p>

<p>All care recipients will be automatically assessed under the post 1 July 2014 means assessment scheme if they have&#58; </p>
		<ul>		<li>
moved from home care into residential care (or vice versa), and/or </li>
		<li>
spent more than 28 days outside of care (not on approved leave)</li>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
		</ul>

<p></p>

<p>The <a href="../older-australians/065-21050552-05.html">Resources</a> page contains links to forms and external websites including Department of Health and Aged Care, My Aged Care and Services Australia. </p>

<p></p>
